<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-753-773  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 753 773.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  July 3 1989 v3 n27 p22(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Plan early for contract modifications.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Townes, Eben.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The modification of government contracts with the intent ofupgrading to acquire enhanced and cost-efficient products is acomplex process which calls for careful planning to avoidprocurement obstacles.andP;  But while the use of newer technologiescan benefit the agency's mission, incorporating them intocontracts can strain acquisition fundamentals.andP;  The key is todetermine if the modification exceeds the original intent of thecontract, making a new announcement in the Commerce Business Dailyand a new Delegation of Procurement Authority (DPA) necessary.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Goals and ObjectivesGovernment ContractsUpgradingCompetitionPurchasing SystemsPlanning.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>